The paper discusses the challenges and issues related to data stream clustering, which involves analyzing and extracting patterns from continuously inserted and queried massive amounts of data. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
